@startuml
title Example agent collaboration chain

skinparam SwimlaneBorderColor #999999
skinparam SwimlaneFontStyle bold

|Human Operator|
start
: Prepare project space;
: Collect initial ideas, requirements, ... ;
: Add these to project in plain text format;

|Synthesizer Sam|
:Review existing materials
(requirements, notes, style guides);
:Extract rules, constraints
and vocabulary;
:Produce condensed spec
for downstream agents;


|Architect Alphonso|
repeat
  :Design high-level architecture (components, flows, boundaries);
  :Document key trade-offs and constraints;
|Human Operator|
  :Review architecture;
  : Provide feedback and additional clarifications;
|Architect Alphonso|
  backward:process feedback and \nrevise assumptions / interpretations;
|Human Operator|
repeat while (Architecture acceptable?) is (no) not (yes)

|Planning Petra|
:Transform architecture into
delivery plan (tasks, milestones,
dependencies);
|Human Operator|
:Review and adjust plan if needed;
#palegreen: Sign off on final design and plan;


split
    |Backend Benny|
    : Write acceptance tests \n based on architecture;
    :Implement backend changes \n and refactors;
    :Update tests / small \n implementation details;
split again
    |DevOps Danny|
    :Update CI/CD pipelines,
    deployment steps, observability \n  and safeguards;
end split

'
|Architect Alphonso|
:Validate implementation against
architecture and constraints;
'
'
|Editor Eddy|
:Convert engineering logs and notes \ninto a management-ready debrief;

|Human Operator|
: Review final debrief;
: Approve and archive project artefacts;

stop

@enduml